node.text:
By @grillhunters 
.
Have you ever had a grilled romaine salad before? If not, you’re in for a unique and delicious smoky surprise.

Here’s a list of ingredients for the marinade and salad. Full recipe with instruction is on the blog.

// Garlic & herbs marinade //
- 3/4 cup olive oil
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tbsp basil, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp chives, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp rosemary, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp parsley, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp lemon zest
- 3 garlic cloves, minced
- 1/2 tsp chili powder
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 tsp black pepper

// Grilles Romaine Salad //
- 1 heart romaine lettuce cut in half lengthwise 
- ½ cup Parmesan cheese flakes
- 4 slice bacon grilled and crispy
- 4 tbsp olive oil extra virgin
- 1 tbsp kosher salt
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tsp back pepper
- ½ lemon zest

#NomadGrills #grillhunters #grilledlettuce #grilledsalad #vealchop #grilledvealchops #smokedveal

node.text:
from Scratch! 🇲🇦😍🍆🍅🔥
This dish is a must and the flavors are amazing!
🕌: Fez, Morocco
🎥: @foodyfetish #foodyfetishoriginal 
Tag a Friend that would love this dish!👇🏼
.

Ingredients
* 1 large eggplant (peeled and chopped*)
* 4 large tomatoes (peeled, seeded and chopped)
* 3 cloves of garlic (finely chopped or pressed)
* 1/3 cup chopped fresh cilantro and parsley (mixed)
* 1 tablespoon paprika
* 1 tablespoon cumin
* 1 1/2 teaspoons salt
* 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional)
* 1/4 cup olive oil
* 1/3 cup water
* Small wedge of lemon (optional)

To Make the Zaalouk:
* Mix all ingredients in a large, deep skillet or pot. Cover and simmer over medium to medium-high heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Adjust the heat if necessary to avoid burning the zaalouk.  Use a spoon or potato masher to crush and blend the tomatoes and eggplant. If you like, a small wedge of lemon can be added to the pan at this time. Continue simmering, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until the liquids are reduced and the zaalouk can be stirred into a heap in the center of the pan.

node.text:
This post goes out to all my apple lovers around the world 🍎🍏 Let me just say I am one of them 🙋‍♀️…Made by @meowmeix
.⠀⠀⠀⁠
Honestly, I can believe how many different varieties there are out there! This isn’t even all of them. I encourage you to try them all and find the varieties you fall in love with.⠀⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⠀⁠
Apples aren’t just delicious, they’re also very nutritious. Apples are packed with water and fiber which both can help you feel fuller for longer. Additionally, apples contain vitamin C, polyphenols, and a type of fiber called pectin that acts as a prebiotic, meaning it feeds your good gut bacteria. To get the most benefits, eat the whole apple, both the skin and flesh.⠀⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⠀⁠
Curious if you have a favorite apple? It’s almost too hard for me to pick.⠀⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⠀l
.⁠⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠

node.text:
Here’s Five delicious and easy Protein options Dinner! Recipes below👩🏻‍🍳 Salmon, Chicken, Prawns, Scallops or Eggs.. Which is your favourite?!😍... By @sara.haven
⠀
⠀
All dishes approximately 500 CALORIES
⠀
⠀
🍣SALMON🍣
with hasselback potatoes.
HOW TO MAKE THE PERFECT CRISPY SALMON:
Honey garlic chipotle salmon 1) combine 1 tbsp honey, 1/4 tsp. chipotle chili powder, 1 tbsp. melted butter, s+p. Spread over two 4-6 oz. fillets 2) in a pan, heat 1 tsp oil; add salmon, skin side up, and sear for 3 mins; flip, and cook an additional 3-4 mins •• crispy garlic-parmesan hasselback potato •• grilled asparagus w/ parmesan and red pepper.
⠀
⠀
🍗CHICKEN🍗
mac n’ cheese
(the coziest of cozy comfort food, amiright?), paired it with cast iron-cooked lemon-honey-garlic-sage chicken + grilled broccolini for a noodle night done right 💯☺️ macaroni & cheese •• lemon honey garlic sage chicken 🌿🍋 •• grilled broccoli parmesan & red pepper 🥦
⠀
⠀
🍤 PRAWNS 🍤
🔥SPICY Garlic Cajun Shrimp
Almond flour fettuccine tossed in olive oil, dried basil, dried sage, and parmesan •• grilled asparagus w/ parmesan.
⠀
⠀
🥘SCALLOPS🥘
The juuuicest seared garlic ghee scallops
Seared in butter with lots of extra garlic👌🏻
Season with garlic salt; in a pan, heat 1 tsp. avocado oil + 1 tsp. garlic ghee; add scallops + sear until lightly brown; flip and sear other side 2 mins •• grilled asparagus w/ parmesan •• garlic-sage fettuccine (toss fettuccine in olive oil, basil, sage, garlic, and parmesan).
⠀
⠀
🍳EGGS AND HALLOUMI🍳
buttery avo toast and 2 eggs
•• good seed thin sliced, toasted + topped with smashed avocado + a drizzle of truffle oil + feta cheese •• sautéed spinach w/ red pepper & parmesan •• grilled halloumi cheese
⠀
⠀

Who loves fancy bread meals!?..This could be lunch for breakfast! 😋

Pick your fav by @toastedtable …1,2,3,4,5 or 6?

Toast 1- whole grain, smashed avocado 🥑, goat cheese, local cherry tomatoes, mint + dill, chili-flakes & @mikeshothoney 🔥

Toast 2- Whole grain loaf, smashed 🥑, smashed hard-boiled eggs, olives, mint, sesame & aleppo pepper 🤪

Toast 3- Sprouted bread, smashed 🥑, sliced peaches, seared halloumi, sesame + nigella seeds, honey 🍯

Toast 4- Sprouted bread, smashed 🥑 avocado, ricotta whipped with preserved lemon 🍋+cinnamon + honey, fresh black figs, dill, cracked black pepper & extra honey 🍯

Toast 5- seeded bread, smashed 🥑 avocado, miso-ginger glazed salmon, extra sesame seeds + cilantro ☺️

Toast 6- a little bagel-inspired, homemade seeded bread, smashed 🥑 avocado, labneh, everything but the bagel smoked salmon, extra everything bagel seasoning, dill & cilantro 😋.

💯 However... the #1 factor that always determines body weight is   
  
ENERGY BALANCE! ⚡️  
  
Your calories in, vs your calories out.  
  
⬆️ The factors above can influence your calorie intake and your calorie output.  
  
The reason for your current body weight is your calorie consumption vs your calorie output.  
 
☝️ It sometimes feels easier to blame other factors, this is why the team are so passionate about people understanding energy balance and the role it plays on body composition.  
  
❌@bodysmartfitness are never there to judge, just because calories in vs calories out is the science, doesn't make it easy to adhere to.

Roasted Shrimp & Veggie Salad 

Lets get some veggies in and lets get some protein in!…By @buzzfeedtasty

📝 Ingredients
( 2 servings)
* 1 cup cherry tomato, sliced
* 1 cup shredded carrot
* 1 cup yellow bell pepper, diced
* 1 cup red onion, diced
* 1 cup asparagus, diced
* 1 lb shrimp
* olive oil, to coat
* chili powder, to taste
* 1 teaspoon fresh oregano, to taste
* salt, to taste
* pepper, to taste
* lime juice, to taste
* 1 large handful mixed greens. 

📝 CHILI LIME VINAIGRETTE DRESSING
* 3 tablespoons lime juice
* 2 tablespoons olive oil
* 1 tablespoon honey
* ½ teaspoon chili powder
* salt, to taste
* pepper, to taste

👨‍🍳 Preparation
1. Preheat oven to 400˚F (200˚C). 

2. Add cut vegetables to a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. 

3. Drizzle in olive oil and sprinkle with seasonings to your preference. Bake for 10 minutes. 

4. Move veggies to the side to make space in the center of the baking sheet and add shrimp in a single layer. 

5. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with seasonings and lime juice to your preference. Bake for 5-8 minutes, until shrimp is fully cooked. Be careful not to overcook. 

6. Mix dressing ingredients together in a small bowl. 

7. In a large salad bowl, combine mixed greens, roasted shrimp, veggies, and vinaigrette dressing together. 

8. Enjoy!

🔍Nutrition Info
* Calories 668
* Fat 32g
* Carbs 47g
* Fiber 8g
* Sugar 27g
* Protein 52g

Delicious garlic butter corn ribs! These are so easy to make and are perfect for a fun and crunchy snack….By @earthofmariaa

Give them a go and serve with a dip of your choice for ultimate deliciousness 🤩

2 corn on the cob
1/4 cup dairy-free butter
3 minced garlic cloves
1/2 tsp paprika
1/2 tsp salt 

Preheat the oven to 180 degrees C/350 F. Remove the leaves from the corn, place it on the table wide side down and halve, then halve again. Mix together the butter, garlic, paprika and salt. Brush the garlic butter over the corn, lay out on the baking tray, and bake for 10-12 minutes, until crispy.
